PublicRemarks:
Silver Springs Shores as a potentially growing area with opportunities for businesses, dining options, and new neighborhoods. I have hundreds available for negotiation. To get detailed information on each lot's zoning and utility status, you'll need to engage in thorough due diligence. Contact the local planning or zoning department to inquire about the zoning regulations for each lot. This will help you understand how the land can be used. Reach out to the local utility companies to verify the availability of essential services such as water, electricity, gas, and sewage on each lot.

Consider hiring a professional land surveyor to provide accurate information about the boundaries and topography of each lot.  Investigate any potential environmental concerns in the area, such as flood zones, soil quality, or protected habitats. If possible, conduct site visits to get a firsthand look at the lots and their surroundings. This can provide valuable insights into the local environment.
Remember, due diligence is crucial in real estate transactions, and thorough research will help you make informed decisions and negotiate effectively.

PublicRemarks:
Ready to Negotiate? A must-see for anyone looking for a peaceful and spacious place to call home. The location in Citra, east of downtown, offers the best of both worlds: a serene countryside setting with the convenience of being just 40 minutes from Gainesville or Ocala. The fact that it's situated just outside of the Ocala National Forest is also a great advantage for outdoor enthusiasts and families who enjoy outdoor activities.
The home itself offers just under 1800 sq ft of living space, which is plenty of room for a family to spread out and enjoy. The large living area and well-equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances and ample cabinet and counter space are great features that are sure to impress. The screened-in lanai offers the perfect place to relax and enjoy the beautiful views of the backyard.
The large master bedroom with dual sinks, stand-up shower, and soaking tub is a great place to retreat and unwind after a long day. The tile flooring throughout the home makes for easy cleaning, and the ceiling fans in every room help keep the home cool and comfortable.
The fenced-in yard is a great feature for families or pets, and the fact that the home is located halfway down a dead-end road with no through traffic offers additional privacy and peace of mind. With the home facing North, you'll enjoy plenty of sunlight across the backyard all year round.
Overall, this is a great home in a peaceful location, and I would highly recommend scheduling an appointment to see it in person. I have no doubt that you'll fall in love with all that this home has to offer, and I look forward to helping you make the move to this wonderful property.

PublicRemarks:
This new residential lot is located in the Hog Valley area of Ocala National Forest Campsite. It is approximately 40 minutes away from Ocala. This location offers a rural setting that is ideal for outdoor enthusiasts.

While the site has electricity nearby, the installation of a well and septic system would be necessary for water supply and waste disposal. Wells provide access to water for residential use, and a septic system manages the proper disposal of wastewater.

Living in the Ocala National Forest Campsite area provides ample opportunities for outdoor activities. The forest is known for its natural beauty and offers a range of activities such as four-wheeling, canoeing, and hunting during available seasons. Outdoor enthusiasts can enjoy exploring the forest, observing wildlife, and engaging in various recreational pursuits.

It's important to note that living in a national forest area may come with specific regulations and restrictions, particularly when it comes to hunting and other activities.
